.TH ROG 1 "May 2026" "Version 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rog \- a log reader and monitoring tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rog
[\fI\fB\-I\fR\fP \fIHOST\fP]
[\fB\-k\fP]
[\fB\-d\fP \fIPORT\fP]
[\fB\-f\fP \fIFIFO_PATH\fP]
[\fB\-s\fP]
[\fB\-g\fP \fIPATTERN\fP]
[\fB\-w\fP \fIPATTERN\fP]
[\fB\-v\fP \fIPATTERN\fP]
[\fB\-i\fP]
[\fB\-C\fP \fINUM\fP]
[\fB\-A\fP \fINUM\fP]
[\fB\-B\fP \fINUM\fP]
[\fB\-r\fP \fIFIELDS\fP]
[\fB\-m\fP \fITHEME|NUM\fP]
[\fB\-c\fP]
[\fB\-u\fP]
[\fB\-o\fP \fINUM\fP]
[\fB\-x\fP \fIPATTERN\fP]
[\fB\-p\fP \fIPRESETS\fP]
[\fB\-P\fP]
[\fB\-a\fP \fIPATTERN\fP]
[\fB\-b\fP \fIPATTERN\fP]
[\fB\-l\fP \fINUM\fP]
[\fB\-H\fP]
[\fB\-h\fP]
[\fIfiles...\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Halfway between \fBtail -f\fP and \fBlnav\fP. Rog monitors log files in real-time with
options for filtering, syntax highlighting, and remote serving over TCP.

It supports four operating modes:
.TP
\fBTail mode\fP (default)
Monitor one or more files in real-time. Pass files as positional arguments.
.TP
\fBFIFO mode\fP (\fB\-f\fP)
Create and read from a named pipe at the specified path.
.TP
\fBServer mode\fP (\fB\-s\fP)
Read from any source and serve over TCP to connected clients.
.TP
\fBClient mode\fP (\fB\-k\fP, \fB\-I\fP)
Connect to a rog server and stream its output locally. Using \fB\-I\fP implies client mode.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-I\fP \fIHOST\fP, \fB\-\-ip\fP=\fIHOST\fP
IP address of the server. Using this flag implies client mode (\fB\-k\fP).
.TP
\fB\-k\fP, \fB\-\-client\fP
Read from localhost in client mode (default port 19888).
.TP
\fB\-d\fP \fIPORT\fP, \fB\-\-port\fP=\fIPORT\fP
TCP port number (default: 19888).
.TP
\fB\-f\fP \fIPATH\fP, \fB\-\-fifo\fP=\fIPATH\fP
Create and read from a named pipe at the given path. The FIFO is
automatically removed on exit.
.TP
\fB\-s\fP, \fB\-\-server\fP
Server mode. Defaults to reading from stdin.
.TP
\fB\-g\fP \fIPATTERN\fP, \fB\-\-grep\fP=\fIPATTERN\fP
Only show lines matching the given regex pattern.
.TP
\fB\-w\fP \fIPATTERN\fP, \fB\-\-wgrep\fP=\fIPATTERN\fP
Like \fB\-g\fP, but match whole words only.
.TP
\fB\-v\fP \fIPATTERN\fP, \fB\-\-vrep\fP=\fIPATTERN\fP
Only show lines that do not match the given regex pattern.
.TP
\fB\-i\fP, \fB\-\-icase\fP
Case-insensitive matching for \fB\-g\fP, \fB\-w\fP, and \fB\-v\fP.
.TP
\fB\-C\fP \fINUM\fP, \fB\-\-context\fP=\fINUM\fP
Show \fINUM\fP lines of context around grep matches.
.TP
\fB\-A\fP \fINUM\fP, \fB\-\-after\fP=\fINUM\fP
Show \fINUM\fP lines of context after grep matches.
.TP
\fB\-B\fP \fINUM\fP, \fB\-\-before\fP=\fINUM\fP
Show \fINUM\fP lines of context before grep matches.
.TP
\fB\-r\fP \fIFIELDS\fP, \fB\-\-remove\fP=\fIFIELDS\fP
Remove fields matching \fIfield=value\fP or \fIfield="quoted value"\fP from output.
Multiple fields may be comma-separated.
.TP
\fB\-m\fP \fITHEME|NUM\fP, \fB\-\-theme\fP=\fITHEME|NUM\fP
Set the syntax highlighting colorscheme. Accepts either a theme name
(see below) or a numeric index (0-12). Use \fB\-h\fP to list available themes.
.TP
\fB\-c\fP, \fB\-\-nocolor\fP
Disable syntax highlighting.
.TP
\fB\-u\fP, \fB\-\-truncate\fP
Truncate lines that exceed terminal width.
.TP
\fB\-o\fP \fINUM\fP, \fB\-\-width\fP=\fINUM\fP
Limit output to \fINUM\fP bytes per line.
.TP
\fB\-x\fP \fIPATTERN\fP, \fB\-\-exclude\fP=\fIPATTERN\fP
Exclude files whose names match the given regex pattern.
.TP
\fB\-p\fP \fIPRESETS\fP, \fB\-\-presets\fP=\fIPRESETS\fP
Load additional presets from \fI~/.config/rogrc\fP by key character.
.TP
\fB\-P\fP, \fB\-\-nopreset\fP
Skip loading presets from \fI~/.config/rogrc\fP.
.TP
\fB\-a\fP \fIPATTERN\fP, \fB\-\-start\fP=\fIPATTERN\fP
Only print lines after a matching line is found.
.TP
\fB\-b\fP \fIPATTERN\fP, \fB\-\-stop\fP=\fIPATTERN\fP
Stop printing (and exit if no \fB\-a\fP) after a matching line is found.
.TP
\fB\-l\fP \fINUM\fP, \fB\-\-lines\fP=\fINUM\fP
Print \fINUM\fP more lines after stop pattern before exiting.
.TP
\fB\-H\fP, \fB\-\-parse\-headers\fP
Parse tail-style file headers (\fI==> file <==\fP) in stdin or socket input.
.TP
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
Print the help menu and list of available color themes.
.SH COLOR THEMES
The following 13 themes are available via \fB\-m\fP (by name or index number 0-12):
.TP
\fB0\fP Visual Studio Dark+ (default)
.TP
\fB1\fP 1337
.TP
\fB2\fP DarkNeon
.TP
\fB3\fP Dracula
.TP
\fB4\fP Coldark-Dark
.TP
\fB5\fP Monokai Extended
.TP
\fB6\fP Sublime Snazzy
.TP
\fB7\fP TwoDark
.TP
\fB8\fP base16
.TP
\fB9\fP gruvbox-dark
.TP
\fB10\fP Nord
.TP
\fB11\fP zenburn
.TP
\fB12\fP ansi
.SH CONFIG
Rog reads configuration from \fI~/.config/rogrc\fP. Each line has the format
\fIkey = arguments\fP, where \fIkey\fP can be:
.TP
\fIdefault\fP
Always applied.
.TP
\fIfilename\fP
Applied when that file is passed as a positional argument.
.TP
\fIsingle letter\fP
Invoked with \fB\-p\fP. Multiple presets can be combined with \fB\-p ab\fP to activate both \fIa\fP and \fIb\fP.
.PP
Example \fI~/.config/rogrc\fP:
.IP
\fBdefault = \-m Dracula \-u\fP
.IP
\fBapp.log = \-r date,uid\fP
.IP
\fBa = /var/log/app.log\fP
.IP
\fBb = \-Hk\fP
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Tail multiple log files:
.B rog app.log error.log
.TP
Filter errors with context lines:
.B rog *.log \-g "^ERROR" \-C3
.TP
Stream program output to remote clients:
.B some_program | rog \-s
.TP
Serve a named pipe over TCP:
.B rog \-s \-f /tmp/myfifo
.TP
Connect to a remote rog server:
.B rog \-I 10.0.0.4
.TP
Create a named pipe and read from it:
.B rog \-f /tmp/myfifo
.TP
Remove sensitive fields while monitoring:
.B rog app.log \-r password,token
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.config/rogrc\fP
Preset configuration file (created automatically on first run if missing).
.SH SUDO / DOAS
When run under \fBsudo\fP or \fBdoas\fP, rog resolves the invoking user's home
directory (via \fBSUDO_USER\fP and \fI/etc/passwd\fP) so that \fI~/.config/rogrc\fP is
read from your own home, not root's.
.PP
For \fBdoas\fP to work correctly, add the following to \fI/etc/doas.conf\fP:
.IP
\fBsetenv SUDO_USER $LOGIN\fP
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tail (1),
.BR grep (1),
.BR lnav (1),
.BR bat (1)
